Hedgie Hokey Pokey: Pins and Nettie have been invited to their friend's dance party!
It's Time to Eat Green Bananas and Saltfish: JoJo and Gran Gran are planning on baking a sweet banana loaf for Jared, who's coming to Gran Gran's house for dinner.
It's Time for a Canal Walk: Animated series about an almost five year-old girl and her fun and wise grandmother who always has something planned to do when JoJo comes to visit.
Cuán worries he's not good enough to dance at Céilí Day, but his friends teach him a simple step that helps him build confidence and enjoy the celebration.
With Pip away, the fairies run the café and get creative with wild ingredients - only to learn that while experimenting is fun, not every recipe turns out as planned.
Fun and games with the animals of the forest.
The Giggling Expanse: While delivering space-chick eggs, the crew detours through the mysterious Giggling Expanse - a cosmic laugh trap where only Bubby's unamused attitude can save the day.
Unhappy Birthday: Grooblings don't celebrate birthdays but can Zuzu's friends respect her wishes and give her the non-birthday she's always wanted?
Doodle Girl must help a down-on-his-luck surfer fix his beach shack in time for the Super Sweet Surfathon competition.
The Picky Picnic: The Mixmups go on a picnic adventure but don't know the food that is offered to them. Will they find another way to enjoy the unfamiliar food.
Pippen's Vanishing Voice: Pippen loses her voice before her concert. Can Vida help her get it back in time for her solo?
Tidbit's Watermelon Worry: Tidbit swallows a watermelon seed and worries he's going to grow a watermelon in his tummy.
Twin-Bots: Drew and Jonathan Scott are twins who dream big. With imagination, grit and heart coupled with a big dose of 'twin-spiration', there's no build too big and no problem too small.
Dancing Shoes: When Drew's dance partner is unable to perform at the school talent show, the Dream Factory Crew equips Jonathan with programmed dancing shoes to act as a replacement.
Trevor leads a group hike to the beaver dam and Pontypandy Mountain, but without using a compass or a map either.
Norman, Hannah, Peter and James compete to see who can build the best robot, but a runaway robot leads to a rescue at sea.
The children show how different pollinators get pollen. Mark and Amy show why bumblebees buzz. And they end with a tour of flowers that help feed the planet! (SL)
The children use an egg to show Zoom how blubber helps sea mammals float. Mark blows hard to demonstrate how whales can dive so deep. And Amy takes Zoom to a seal rescue centre. (SL)
